#compdef DPAPImk2john adxcsouf2john apop2john diskcryptor2john ejabberd2john encdatavault2john fvde2john geli2john gitea2john ibmiscanner2john iwork2john keplr2john known_hosts2john krb2john
# Documentation: https://github.com/openwall/john (bleeding-jumbo branch)
#                — sources read directly from run/*.py and run/*.pl
# Reference accessed: 2026-05-30
# John the Ripper *2john helpers, round 4. Extends rounds 144-146 with 14
# more hash extractors covering Windows DPAPI / IBM 4690 / APOP / DiskCryptor /
# ejabberd / EncDataVault / FileVault DriveEnc / FreeBSD GELI / Gitea /
# IBM iSeries / Apple iWork / Keplr / SSH known_hosts / Kerberos PDML.
# Surfaces transcribed from upstream source rather than from Debian
# dyn-redirect manpages (which 404).

local curcontext="$curcontext" state line ret=1

case $service in

  DPAPImk2john)
    # run/DPAPImk2john.py — Windows DPAPI masterkey extractor with the
    # most-complex flag surface of any *2john script so far. Two mutually
    # exclusive operating modes:
    #   - Standard:  -S SID -mk MASTERKEY -c CONTEXT  (all 3 required)
    #   - Preferred: -P PREFERRED  (alone; rejects -mk/-S/-c)
    # The shared --password flag pre-supplies the decrypt key.
    _arguments -s -S \
      '(-P --preferred)-S+[user account SID owning the masterkey]:SID:' \
      '(-P --preferred)--sid=[user account SID owning the masterkey]:SID:' \
      '(-P --preferred)-mk+[masterkey file (%APPDATA%\\Protect\\<SID>)]:file:_files' \
      '(-P --preferred)--masterkey=[masterkey file]:file:_files' \
      '(-P --preferred)-c+[user account context]:context:(domain domain1607+ domain1607- local)' \
      '(-P --preferred)--context=[user account context]:context:(domain domain1607+ domain1607- local)' \
      '(-mk --masterkey -S --sid -c --context)-P+["Preferred" file with active masterkey GUID]:file:_files' \
      '(-mk --masterkey -S --sid -c --context)--preferred=["Preferred" file with active masterkey GUID]:file:_files' \
      '-d[debug output]' \
      '--debug[debug output]' \
      '--password=[masterkey decryption password]:password:' \
      && ret=0
    ;;

  adxcsouf2john)
    # run/adxcsouf2john.py — IBM/Toshiba 4690 OS ADXCSOUF.DAT / ADXEPW0F.DAT.
    # Upstream prints "Tip: Maximum password length is 8 on IBM/Toshiba 4690
    # systems" to stderr.
    _arguments -s -S \
      '*:ADXCSOUF.DAT or ADXEPW0F.DAT:_files -g "*.DAT"' \
      && ret=0
    ;;

  apop2john)
    # run/apop2john.py — APOP challenge/response extractor from pcap.
    # Output format: username:$dynamic_1017$hash$HEX$salt
    _arguments -s -S \
      '*:PCAP file:_files -g "*.(pcap|pcapng|cap)"' \
      && ret=0
    ;;

  diskcryptor2john)
    # run/diskcryptor2john.py — DiskCryptor volume header extractor.
    # Reads first 2048 bytes, calculates entropy, warns if <6 bits/byte.
    # Env-var FORCE=1 overrides entropy warning.
    # Cascaded ciphers NOT supported.
    _arguments -s -S \
      '*:DiskCryptor encrypted device or raw image:_files' \
      && ret=0
    ;;

  ejabberd2john)
    # run/ejabberd2john.py — parses files generated by `ejabberdctl dump`.
    _arguments -s -S \
      '*:ejabberdctl dump file:_files' \
      && ret=0
    ;;

  encdatavault2john)
    # run/encdatavault2john.py — single VAULT FOLDER (not a file).
    _arguments -s -S \
      '1:ENCSecurity DataVault folder:_files -/' \
      && ret=0
    ;;

  fvde2john)
    # run/fvde2john.py — single FileVault Drive Encryption disk image.
    # Uses argparse, so exactly 1 required positional.
    _arguments -s -S \
      '1:FileVault disk image:_files' \
      && ret=0
    ;;

  geli2john)
    # run/geli2john.py — FreeBSD GELI metadata extractor (1+ disk images).
    # Seeks to last 1024 bytes, looks for GEOM::ELI magic, supports AES-XTS
    # and AES-CBC, metadata versions 0-7.
    _arguments -s -S \
      '*:GELI disk image:_files' \
      && ret=0
    ;;

  gitea2john)
    # run/gitea2john.py — STDIN-driven Gitea pbkdf2-sha256 hash converter.
    # Input format on stdin: username:hex_salt:hex_hash:algorithm
    # Where algorithm = pbkdf2$iterations$keylen.
    # Has -h/--help. Typical pipeline:
    #   sqlite3 gitea.db 'SELECT name, salt, passwd, passwd_hash_algo FROM user;' | gitea2john.py
    _arguments -s -S \
      '(- *)-h[show usage docstring and exit]' \
      '(- *)--help[show usage docstring and exit]' \
      && ret=0
    ;;

  ibmiscanner2john)
    # run/ibmiscanner2john.py — IBM iSeries (ibmiscanner output) → AS400-SHA.
    # Input lines: username:hexhash → username:$as400ssha1$hexhash$username
    _arguments -s -S \
      '*:ibmiscanner output file:_files' \
      && ret=0
    ;;

  iwork2john)
    # run/iwork2john.py — Apple iWork .key files (iWork '09 and 2013/2014).
    _arguments -s -S \
      '*:Apple iWork file:_files -g "*.(key|numbers|pages)"' \
      && ret=0
    ;;

  keplr2john)
    # run/keplr2john.py — Keplr Chrome-extension LevelDB extractor.
    # Required 1st arg: wallet folder. Optional 2nd arg: password (when
    # supplied the script attempts decryption rather than just dumping).
    # Note: first arg must NOT begin with a hyphen.
    _arguments -s -S \
      '1:Keplr wallet folder (Chrome extension data):_files -/' \
      '2:optional password to attempt decryption:' \
      && ret=0
    ;;

  known_hosts2john)
    # run/known_hosts2john.py — hashed-entry extractor from SSH known_hosts.
    # Lines starting "|1|" → stdout as $known_hosts$<data>.
    # Non-hashed entries → stderr.
    _arguments -s -S \
      '*:SSH known_hosts file:_files' \
      && ret=0
    ;;

  krb2john)
    # run/krb2john.py — Kerberos hash extractor from PDML files.
    # Generate input via: tshark -r capture.pcap -T pdml > sample.pdml
    _arguments -s -S \
      '*:PDML file from tshark:_files -g "*.pdml"' \
      && ret=0
    ;;

esac

return ret
